    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients ventilated for more than 24 hours

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients less than 16 years of age patients who receive only non-invasive ventilation
             patients chronically ventilated at time of ICU admission patients who will not be
             candidates for weaning from ventilation at time of admission If withdrawl of life
             support is imminent at the point the patient has been ventilated for 24 hours
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
